      "source": [
        "### 5.2 The aspiration gap — use vs. want by use case\n",
        "\n",
        "At the use-case level, the pattern is already visible: **the largest gaps are not in content generation.** They are in the more operational forms of AI work: organizing information, automating tasks, interpreting data, and predicting outcomes.\n",
        "\n",
        "This is the first clue that the nonprofit AI bottleneck is no longer basic exposure to LLMs. It is the ability to apply AI to work that depends on data, workflows, and internal systems.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 15,
      "id": "cfa33fb1",
      "metadata": {
        "execution": {
          "iopub.execute_input": "2026-04-27T07:11:56.239040Z",
          "iopub.status.busy": "2026-04-27T07:11:56.238751Z",
          "iopub.status.idle": "2026-04-27T07:11:56.580510Z",
          "shell.execute_reply": "2026-04-27T07:11:56.579473Z"
        },
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 554
        },
        "id": "cfa33fb1",
        "outputId": "bcf2a6c6-a091-4aa2-e751-c00e9812dcd2"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 1100x600 with 1 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {}
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Compute use% and want% per category\n",
        "use_pct  = [df[f'use_{c}'].mean()  * 100 for c in CATEGORIES]\n",
        "want_pct = [df[f'want_{c}'].mean() * 100 for c in CATEGORIES]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Sort by gap, largest first\n",
        "order  = np.argsort([w - u for u, w in zip(use_pct, want_pct)])[::-1]\n",
        "cats_o = [CATEGORIES[i] for i in order]\n",
        "use_o  = [use_pct[i]    for i in order]\n",
        "want_o = [want_pct[i]   for i in order]\n",
        "\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(11, 6), facecolor=PAPER)\n",
        "y = np.arange(len(cats_o))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Connecting lines + gap labels\n",
        "for i, (u, w) in enumerate(zip(use_o, want_o)):\n",
        "    ax.plot([u, w], [i, i], color=MUTED, linewidth=2, alpha=0.4, zorder=1)\n",
        "    ax.text((u + w) / 2, i + 0.28, f'+{w - u:.0f}', ha='center',\n",
        "            fontsize=10, color=INK2, fontweight='bold', style='italic')\n",
        "\n",
        "ax.scatter(use_o,  y, color=CORAL, s=240, zorder=3, label='Currently doing', edgecolor=PAPER, linewidth=2)\n",
        "ax.scatter(want_o, y, color=TEAL,  s=240, zorder=3, label='Want to do',     edgecolor=PAPER, linewidth=2)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Value labels at the dots\n",
        "for i, (u, w) in enumerate(zip(use_o, want_o)):\n",
        "    ax.text(u - 2, i, f'{u:.0f}%', ha='right', va='center', fontsize=10, color=INK, fontweight='bold')\n",
        "    ax.text(w + 2, i, f'{w:.0f}%', ha='left',  va='center', fontsize=10, color=INK, fontweight='bold')\n",
        "\n",
        "ax.set_yticks(y)\n",
        "ax.set_yticklabels(cats_o, fontsize=12)\n",
        "ax.invert_yaxis()\n",
        "ax.set_xlim(-2, 75)\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel('% of respondents', fontsize=11)\n",
        "ax.legend(loc='lower right', frameon=False, fontsize=11)\n",
        "style_ax(ax, grid_axis='x')\n",
        "ax.grid(axis='y', visible=False)\n",
        "ax.set_title('The aspiration gap: caught up on ChatGPT — stalled on everything else',\n",
        "             fontsize=14, loc='left', pad=18)\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]
    },
    {
