      "source": [
        "**The pattern is striking:**\n",
        "\n",
        "| Use case | Heavy Adopters use | Latent Adopters want |\n",
        "|---|---|---|\n",
        "| Generate content | **87%** | 75% |\n",
        "| Chatbot Q&A | **72%** | 54% |\n",
        "| Translate / transcribe | 60% | 55% |\n",
        "| Automate tasks | 48% | **81%** |\n",
        "| Organize data | 56% | **84%** |\n",
        "| Interpret data | 51% | 58% |\n",
        "| Predict outcomes | 35% | **70%** |\n",
        "\n",
        "The dashed line is meaningful. Above it (creative use cases): Heavy Adopters dominate by 12-18 points. Below it (operational use cases): Latent Adopters' demand outpaces Heavy Adopters' actual usage by 28-35 points.\n",
        "\n",
        "**This is not the same shape of demand at different speeds.** It's a *different shape*. Latent Adopters aren't lagging Heavy Adopters — they're trying to do AI work Heavy Adopters haven't started doing.\n",
        "\n",
        "**61% of Latent Adopters' wants are operational** (predict, organize, automate, interpret). **Only 46% of Heavy Adopters' uses are operational.** The would-be next wave is more enterprise-oriented than the current adopter base.\n",
        "\n",
        "### 9.3 Why this matters: the LLM-API ceiling\n",
        "\n",
        "Generative content, chatbots, and translation are use cases where you can drop in a third-party LLM (ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini) and get value with minimal data infrastructure. **You don't need clean databases to write a fundraising email.**\n",
        "\n",
        "Operational AI is different. To \"predict outcomes\" or \"organize our information,\" an organization needs:\n",
        "- structured data\n",
        "- a pipeline to clean and feed that data\n",
        "- staff who can wire models to it\n",
        "- governance that lets data leave (or stay)\n",
        "\n",
        "The Heavy Adopter cohort caught up on creative AI by adopting tools the AI industry built *for the consumer market*. The Latent Adopters are looking for tools the AI industry hasn't built yet — or has built only for enterprise budgets.\n",
        "\n",
        "### 9.4 The diagnosis: stalled at the threshold\n",
        "\n",
        "If Latent Adopters look identical to Heavy Adopters on attitudes, what differs? Compare the infrastructure profile of FW against the **Literacy Gap** cohort — both are non-users, but the Literacy Gap cohort doesn't even feel literate enough to evaluate AI."
      ]
    },
