      "source": [
        "The Latent Adopters have **2× the tech-staff coverage** of the Literacy Gap cohort (34% vs 16%) and substantially more cloud storage (60% vs 48%). They're not lost — they have the foundation. They're stuck on the *last layer*: the org-level permission, the workflow integration, the trusted vendor relationship that turns infrastructure into action.\n",
        "\n",
        "This is the cohort the deck's infrastructure thesis was actually about. Not orgs that need AI tools — orgs that have the will, the comfort, the aspiration, and the partial stack, and need the **last rung** of the ladder built for them.\n",
        "\n",
        "### 9.5 Voices: what they actually say\n",
